          },
          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Radiochemical studies of the fast neutron fission of",
                "uranium-235 and uranium-238"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "L.R.Bunney",
                "E.M.Scadden",
                "J.O.Abriam",
                "N.E.Ballou"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "C,58GENEVA,15,449,1958",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "C,58GENEVA,15,449,1958",
                    "doi": null,
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "C",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "58GENEVA",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "15",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "449"
                      },
                      "date": 1958
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USANRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USACLA"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 60-in. cyclotron at the",
                "University of California"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets were stacks of uranium foil which had",
                "been enriched (93.5% U235) or depleted (0.031% U235)",
                "in U235. These foil stacks were enclosed in cadmium",
                "sheet 0.75-mm thick to filter out the thermal neutrons",
                "present. These target assemblies were placed in the",
                "cyclotron behind a beryllium target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Side-window, gas-flow, proportional counters."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " After irradiation, the uranium foils were",
                "dissolved in 6 N HNO3. The final precipitates were",
                "collected on 23-mm filter paper. A filter tower was",
                "used, which defined a sample area 20 mm in diameter.",
                "The filter papers were mounted on brass planchets",
                "3/8-in. thick and covered with thin  pliofilm (about",
                "1 mg/cm2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "No information on uncertainty.  The precision of the",
                "radiochemical analyses is about 5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The counting rates were corrected for chemical yield,",
                "decay from the end of the irradiation to the time of",
                "counting, the length of irradiation, and the counting",
                "shelf if it differed from the \"standard\" shelf.",
                "An empirical correction for self-scattering and",
                "self-absorption was made by plotting observed specific",
                "activity vs. sample weight for samples made up from the",
                "same solution of each radionuclide of interest and",
                "normalizing to a convenient sample weight. In this way",
                "these corrections were kept smaller than 10% in all",
                "cases."
              ]
            }
          ],
